definitions: in a state of mental or nervous strain with muscles tight from stress
relating to verb forms that indicate when an action takes place in time
examples: The atmosphere was tense before the announcement
Her shoulders were tense from sitting at the computer
The past tense shows actions that already happened
Students often struggle with the present perfect tense

definitions: relating to or denoting the force required to stretch something until it breaks
examples: The bridge cables have incredible tensile strength
Engineers tested the tensile properties of the new material

definitions: done without confidence, showing hesitation or uncertainty in manner or approach
not certain or fixed that may be changed or confirmed later
examples: She made a tentative step onto the ice
His tentative smile showed he wasn't sure of the reception
We have a tentative agreement pending final approval
The schedule is tentative and subject to change

definitions: coming after nine others in counting order or position in a sequence
examples: She finished tenth in the marathon race
This is the tenth time I've explained this

definitions: very weak or slight, lacking substance or strength, barely holding together
examples: Their connection was tenuous at best after years apart
The evidence supporting his theory was extremely tenuous

definitions: having a permanent post, especially as a teacher or professor at a university
examples: The tenured professor could speak freely without fear
She became a tenured faculty member after six years

definitions: only slightly warm, lukewarm, neither hot nor cold in temperature
showing little enthusiasm or interest, halfhearted in response or feeling
examples: The coffee had gone tepid while she worked
The bath water was tepid and uncomfortable
The audience gave a tepid response to the performance
His tepid support for the project was obvious

definitions: forming or situated at the end or extremity of something
predicted to lead to death, incurable and fatal in medical conditions
examples: The terminal station is where all trains must stop
We met at the terminal gate before boarding
The doctor diagnosed him with terminal cancer
She provided care for terminal patients at the hospice

definitions: brought to an end, stopped, or concluded, often referring to employment or contracts
examples: His employment was terminated due to budget cuts
The terminated contract left both parties free to negotiate

definitions: consisting of three parts or elements, based on the number three
examples: The ternary form in music has three distinct sections
Computer scientists use ternary logic with three possible values

definitions: of or relating to the earth or its inhabitants as opposed to space
living on or in the ground rather than in water, trees, or air
examples: Terrestrial television broadcasts from ground-based transmitters
Scientists study both terrestrial and marine ecosystems
Frogs are amphibians but many species are primarily terrestrial
Terrestrial mammals evolved from creatures that left the sea

definitions: feeling intense fear, extremely frightened to the point of being unable to move or think clearly
examples: The terrified child hid behind her mother
He was terrified of speaking in public

definitions: causing extreme fear or terror, frightening to a very high degree
examples: The terrifying storm destroyed everything in its path
She had a terrifying experience while hiking alone

definitions: relating to the ownership or control of an area of land or sea
tending to defend an area against intruders, protective of one's space or domain
examples: The territorial dispute between the countries lasted decades
They respected each other's territorial waters
Cats are very territorial animals marking their space
He became territorial about his office when newcomers arrived

definitions: using very few words, abrupt in manner, brief to the point of rudeness
examples: His terse reply indicated he was still angry
The manager's terse email left everyone confused

definitions: third in order or level, coming after primary and secondary in importance or development
examples: She pursued tertiary education at the university level
This is only a tertiary concern after safety and cost

definitions: decorated with a pattern of repeated shapes that fit together without gaps or overlaps
examples: The tessellated floor featured intricate geometric designs
Artists created tessellated patterns inspired by Islamic architecture

definitions: tried and proven reliable through experience or examination, subjected to testing
examples: This is a tested method that always produces results
The tested formula has been used for generations

definitions: relating to or affecting the testicles, the male reproductive glands
examples: Regular testicular examinations can detect cancer early
The doctor specialized in testicular health issues

definitions: relating to or constituting testimony, especially a formal statement praising someone's character or qualifications
examples: The company website featured testimonial videos from satisfied customers
She received a glowing testimonial letter from her supervisor

definitions: tied with a rope or chain to restrict movement, connected or linked to something
examples: The horse was tethered to the fence post
Her phone was tethered to her laptop for internet

definitions: relating to fabrics or the production of fabrics through weaving or knitting
examples: The textile industry employs millions of workers worldwide
She studied textile design at the art college

definitions: relating to or based on a text or texts, concerning written material
examples: The scholar performed detailed textual analysis of the manuscript
They found several textual errors in the first edition

definitions: having a particular texture or feel, not smooth but with a distinctive surface quality
examples: The textured wallpaper added depth to the room
She preferred textured fabrics over smooth ones

definitions: feeling or expressing gratitude, pleased and relieved about something
examples: I'm thankful for your help during this difficult time
She was thankful the accident wasn't more serious

definitions: having become liquid or soft after being frozen, warmed from a frozen state
examples: The thawed chicken was ready to cook
Once thawed, the pipes started working again

definitions: relating to acting, actors, or the theater as a form of entertainment
exaggerated and excessively dramatic in manner, intended to attract attention
examples: Her theatrical training showed in every performance
The theatrical production required months of preparation
His theatrical gestures made everyone laugh
She made a theatrical exit slamming the door

definitions: relating to or characterized by belief in the existence of a god or gods
examples: Most theistic religions share certain moral principles
His theistic worldview influenced all his decisions

definitions: relating to or based on subjects or themes, connected by a common topic or idea
examples: The museum organized a thematic exhibition on climate change
Teachers used thematic units to integrate different subjects

definitions: relating to or denoting a system of government in which priests or religious leaders rule in the name of God
examples: Some ancient civilizations had theocratic governments
The theocratic state enforced religious laws

definitions: relating to the study of religion and religious belief, concerning the nature of God and religious truth
examples: She pursued theological studies at the seminary
The theological debate continued for hours

definitions: concerned with theories rather than their practical applications, existing only in theory
examples: His approach was purely theoretic without practical testing
The theoretic framework needed real-world validation

definitions: relating to the healing of disease or having a beneficial effect on the body or mind
examples: Massage has therapeutic benefits for sore muscles
She found gardening to be therapeutic after stressful days

definitions: relating to heat or temperature, caused by or producing heat
examples: The thermal imaging camera detected heat signatures
She wore thermal underwear in the cold weather

definitions: relating to nuclear reactions occurring at very high temperatures, especially in hydrogen bombs or stellar cores
examples: The sun generates energy through thermonuclear fusion
Scientists studied thermonuclear reactions in laboratory conditions

definitions: relating to drama and the theater, especially in a formal or affected way
examples: Her thespian talents were evident from childhood
The thespian society performed Shakespeare every summer

definitions: made or become thick or thicker in consistency, increased in density or viscosity
examples: The sauce thickened after simmering for an hour
His thickened arteries required immediate medical attention

definitions: becoming thick or thicker, increasing in density, width, or consistency
examples: The thickening fog made driving dangerous
Add flour as a thickening agent to the soup

definitions: given to stealing, characterized by theft or the practice of stealing
examples: The thieving raccoons raided our garbage every night
His thieving ways finally landed him in jail

definitions: made or become less thick, dense, or numerous by removal or reduction
examples: The thinned paint spread more easily
The crowd had thinned by midnight

definitions: coming after two others in counting order, position, or time
examples: She came in third place in the competition
This is my third attempt at the recipe

definitions: feeling a need to drink, having a dry mouth and throat from lack of liquid
having a strong desire for something, eagerly wanting or craving
examples: The thirsty runners grabbed water at every station
Working in the heat made everyone thirsty
She was thirsty for knowledge about different cultures
The thirsty soil absorbed the rain immediately

definitions: equivalent to the sum of six and seven, one more than twelve
examples: There were thirteen people at the dinner table
Many buildings skip the thirteenth floor

definitions: coming after twelve others in counting order or position
examples: Friday the thirteenth is considered unlucky by some
The thirteenth amendment abolished slavery

definitions: coming after twenty-nine others in counting order or position
examples: They celebrated their thirtieth wedding anniversary
The thirtieth day of April ends the month

definitions: equivalent to three times ten, the number between twenty-nine and thirty-one
examples: The meeting will last thirty minutes
She just turned thirty years old yesterday

definitions: having many thorns or sharp projections, prickly with pointed growths
causing difficulty or disagreement, presenting problems that are hard to solve
examples: The thorny rose bush scratched her arms
Thorny desert plants protect themselves from animals
Immigration remains a thorny political issue
They faced the thorny problem of budget allocation

definitions: complete with regard to every detail, not superficial or partial, performed comprehensively
examples: The detective conducted a thorough investigation
She did a thorough job cleaning the house

definitions: a horse of pure breed, especially one bred for racing with documented ancestry
of outstanding quality, showing characteristics of good breeding or refinement
examples: The thoroughbred horse won three major races
They visited a thoroughbred breeding farm in Kentucky
She had the thoroughbred elegance of old aristocracy
His thoroughbred manners impressed everyone at dinner

definitions: showing consideration for the needs of other people, kind and helpful
engaged in or involving deep thought, contemplative and reflective in manner
examples: His thoughtful gesture of bringing flowers brightened her day
She was always thoughtful about remembering birthdays
He had a thoughtful expression while solving the puzzle
Her thoughtful analysis revealed new insights
